# Task Management Rules

## Overview
This document defines the rules and guidelines for task management in the project.

## Task Organization
- Tasks should be organized in the `tasks` directory
- Each task should have a unique identifier
- Tasks should include clear acceptance criteria
- Tasks should be prioritized based on business value

## Task Workflow
1. Task Creation
   - Create task with clear description
   - Assign priority and complexity
   - Add acceptance criteria
   - Link to related issues/PRs

2. Task Progress
   - Update status regularly
   - Document blockers
   - Track time spent
   - Update dependencies

3. Task Completion
   - Verify acceptance criteria
   - Update documentation
   - Close related issues
   - Update changelog

## Best Practices
- Keep tasks focused and atomic
- Use clear, actionable language
- Include relevant context
- Track dependencies
- Regular status updates
- Document decisions
